eekly magazines in morocco telquel and nishan benchemsi brought controversial and taboo subjects to the public's attention often incriminating the king himself in these revealing articles benchemsi shares the details of how the regime bankrupted his publications and drove a generation of avant garde journalists out of morocco the kingdom of paradox appeared in nieman reports november 8 2011 by ahmed benchemsi related links html+ nieman report morocco and press freedom a complicated relationship http www nieman harvard edu repor html+ nieman report the ups and downs of two pioneering magazines http www nieman harvard edu repor search cddrl search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages news of interest larry diamond releases a new book the spirit of democracy the struggle to build free societies throughout the world january 22 2008 cddrl fsi stanford news michael mcfaul talks to npr talk of the nation about the recent revival of russia's military power in the news npr talk of the nation on august 22 2007 the putin paradox michael a mcfaul center for american progress on june 20 2004 cddrl director michael mcfaul speaks on the challenges in russia after the breakup of the soviet union washington post on december 24 2006 michael mcfaul director of the center on democracy development and the rule of law comments on the political situation in thailand september 21 2006 news michael mcfaul becomes director of the center on democracy development and the rule of law september 2 2005 news support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 4610 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
